Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Lotka-Volterra Model (Prey-Predator)", "Subtitle",
 CellFrame->{{5, 0}, {0, 0}},
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.98338456282423*^9, 3.9833845674600716`*^9}, {
  3.983384759668297*^9, 3.983384782019457*^9}},
 Background->RGBColor[
  0.4, 0.6, 1, 0.33],ExpressionUUID->"d54cb92b-5b44-8040-8dba-01e1b50c9fbc"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A simple, yet usefull, model to describe the dynamics of two interacting \
species, generally a prey (x) and a predator (y), is conformed by a pair of \
first order non-linear coupled differential equations. Proposed by Alfred J. \
Lotka (1925) and Vito Volterra (1926), it models how the growth rate of the \
prey depends on its abundance and the predation, while the growth rate of the \
predator depends on the availability of preys, giving oscilating population \
cycles:\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox["dx", "dt"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", " ", "x"}], "-", 
     RowBox[{"\[Beta]", " ", "x", " ", "y"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"a79cf90b-36e0-1146-83d2-e2ef643591e7"],
 "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox["dy", "dt"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"\[Delta]", " ", "x", " ", "y"}], "-", 
     RowBox[{"\[Gamma]", " ", "y"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "569e41a4-d97c-2e48-b522-4e1f6d54f6ce"],
 "\nwhere \[Alpha] is the maximum prey per capita growth rate, \[Beta] is the \
effect of the presence of predators on the prey death rate,  \[Gamma] is the \
predator\[CloseCurlyQuote]s per capita death rate, and \[Delta] is the effect \
of the presence of prey on the predator\[CloseCurlyQuote]s growth rate.\n\n\
For this problem, suppose the initial conditions:\n\[Alpha] = 1.0 \n\[Beta] = \
0.1\n\[Delta] = 0.075\n\[Gamma] = 1.5\nx[0]= 10.0 (density of preys)\ny[0]= \
5.0 (density of predators)\nWhat density will the populations have after 30 \
time units?\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tT[30]=?\nSince this equation does \
not have an exact solution, solving with NDSolve method is set as the \
reference solution."
}], "Text",
 CellFrame->{{4, 0}, {0, 0}},
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9831021941063385`*^9, {3.9831039177422905`*^9, 3.9831042351264305`*^9}, {
   3.983357797907114*^9, 3.983357811635023*^9}, {3.983357856699135*^9, 
   3.98335788368178*^9}, {3.983359731795574*^9, 3.9833597449305687`*^9}, {
   3.983361787070179*^9, 3.9833617899120007`*^9}, {3.9833619685350037`*^9, 
   3.983362299637684*^9}, {3.983362538949625*^9, 3.9833625608263073`*^9}, {
